WEBVTT

00:00.817 --> 00:02.550
Previously on "Wrecked"...

00:02.575 --> 00:04.484
It's the community pile. I saved it,

00:04.509 --> 00:05.821
and now everyone thinks it's gone.

00:05.846 --> 00:08.026
- What are they fighting over?
- Airline pretzels.

00:08.052 --> 00:09.847
- The only food we have left.
- Will you marry me?

00:09.872 --> 00:11.411
- No.
- Why not?

00:11.436 --> 00:12.771
Because you lied to me, Todd.

00:12.796 --> 00:14.247
And you stole the camp's stuff.

00:14.272 --> 00:15.957
- Whatever, dude.
- Where's our stuff?!

00:15.982 --> 00:18.085
It's all gone! I hid it.

00:18.110 --> 00:23.866
From now on,
I'm the friggin' king of the island!

00:25.123 --> 00:27.486
Come on, Steve. Be strong. Yeah.

00:27.511 --> 00:30.498
"See the world," they said. [Chuckles]

00:30.523 --> 00:32.259
I should never have left Papakura.

00:32.665 --> 00:35.634
Oh, dear! Aah!

00:35.659 --> 00:38.879
Okay, Todd, can I get
that toothbrush now?

00:38.904 --> 00:40.771
You look a little short there, Legs.

00:40.796 --> 00:42.032
You said three nuts!

00:42.056 --> 00:44.602
Oh, yeah, that was before tax.

00:44.628 --> 00:45.915
Now it's four.

00:45.940 --> 00:47.059
Come on, Todd!

00:47.125 --> 00:50.058
My mouth tastes like
a... homeless foot!

00:50.082 --> 00:53.125
You don't like it, go find a Rite-Aid!

00:53.150 --> 00:56.306
I think there's one, like,
a thousand miles that way.

00:56.331 --> 00:57.677
All right, I'll get you another nut!

00:57.703 --> 01:01.226
Of course, now there's also
my handling fee and gratuity.

01:01.251 --> 01:03.369
So why don't you throw in that hat.

01:03.393 --> 01:06.941
But my head is so small.
It will never fit you.

01:06.966 --> 01:08.824
Maybe I'll wipe my ass with it.

01:08.849 --> 01:10.276
It's getting a little chaffed.

01:10.301 --> 01:11.678
[Sighs]

01:11.703 --> 01:15.301
â™ª

01:15.326 --> 01:17.126
There you go.

01:19.491 --> 01:20.947
This is criminal.

01:20.972 --> 01:22.616
Nah, it's within the law.

01:22.641 --> 01:24.130
[Grunts]

01:24.155 --> 01:26.955
The Todd law.

01:26.980 --> 01:28.425
[Laughs]

01:28.450 --> 01:30.060
Go get it!

01:30.275 --> 01:32.942
So that's included in the extra nuts?

01:32.967 --> 01:33.795
No.

01:33.842 --> 01:37.198
- Synced and corrected by martythecrazy -
- www.addic7ed.com -

01:37.223 --> 01:39.779
Just look at him,
hoarding all of our stuff like that.

01:39.803 --> 01:41.969
Todd's unleashed a lot of bad juju.

01:41.994 --> 01:43.088
People are getting desperate.

01:43.113 --> 01:44.248
Yeah, if we're gonna be living here,

01:44.274 --> 01:45.925
we need some basic
rules and regulations.

01:45.950 --> 01:47.856
I just wish there was a way to
get the stuff back from Todd.

01:47.881 --> 01:49.351
I mean...  We could bum-rush him,

01:49.376 --> 01:51.638
take back our stuff with good,
old American force.

01:51.663 --> 01:53.631
We can't. He's got all of
our stuff hidden somewhere

01:53.656 --> 01:54.726
like some kind of rat.

01:54.751 --> 01:56.028
- Danny!
- Hey, guys.

01:56.053 --> 01:57.103
How can I be of service?

01:57.128 --> 01:59.168
You're a cop. Can't you make Todd

01:59.192 --> 02:01.235
give us all our stuff back with your...

02:01.773 --> 02:04.864
Emma, are you suggesting I use
my weapon for intimidation?

02:04.889 --> 02:06.190
Because I would never...

02:06.214 --> 02:07.606
What the hell do you want?

02:07.631 --> 02:09.640
For you to give up the goods, Todd.

02:11.411 --> 02:12.875
Are you threatening me, dude?

02:12.900 --> 02:14.186
What are you gonna do, shoot me?

02:14.211 --> 02:16.751
Hey! Hey, police brutality!

02:16.776 --> 02:18.006
- Danny's gonna shoot me!
- Shh!

02:18.031 --> 02:18.832
No, no, no, no, no!

02:18.857 --> 02:20.976
I can't believe you
would even consider that.

02:21.001 --> 02:22.681
[Scoffs] Civilians.

02:22.706 --> 02:24.316
Karen: Daniel, why
don't you do a stakeout?

02:24.341 --> 02:26.775
Tail him till he leads you to the stash.

02:26.900 --> 02:29.220
A stakeout, brilliant.
Why didn't I think of that?

02:29.245 --> 02:30.483
I could kiss you right now.

02:30.508 --> 02:31.729
- Do it.
- What?

02:31.754 --> 02:33.889
- Do it. Kiss me on the mouth.
- Oh, no, thank you.

02:33.914 --> 02:35.101
Come on. Come right on in.

02:35.126 --> 02:36.066
That's not what I was implying.

02:36.091 --> 02:37.653
You're not coming to
me, I'm coming to you.

02:37.679 --> 02:38.864
- Oh, oh.
- How about this?

02:38.889 --> 02:40.800
Is this close enough to get you enticed?

02:40.825 --> 02:42.937
- Uh, I'm... I'm not... Ohh.
- What about this?

02:42.962 --> 02:45.024
If you want to use your tongue,
I'm not gonna complain.

02:45.049 --> 02:47.474
Okay, I think I'm gonna
go do the stakeout,

02:47.498 --> 02:48.695
if you guys don't mind.

02:48.721 --> 02:52.897
But rest assured,
Todd's gonna lead me right to the stash.

02:52.921 --> 02:54.456
[Chuckles]

02:54.481 --> 02:56.481
[Sea gulls crying]

03:00.066 --> 03:02.485
My, my, my.

03:03.129 --> 03:05.859
Sure it hot out here, isn't it...

03:07.295 --> 03:08.746
Daniel?

03:11.077 --> 03:13.375
Reveal yourself!

03:14.861 --> 03:17.813
Hello, Todd.

03:18.603 --> 03:22.110
I applaud the effort,
but I smelled your beard sweat

03:22.135 --> 03:23.634
from a hundred yards out.

03:24.548 --> 03:28.001
So, what did you think?
I was just gonna slip up

03:28.026 --> 03:29.991
and let you follow me to the stuff?

03:30.016 --> 03:31.230
No.

03:31.255 --> 03:32.667
[Chuckles]

03:32.692 --> 03:34.839
Hilarious.

03:34.865 --> 03:38.267
But I'm not showing you Jimmy Jack Corn.

03:38.515 --> 03:41.421
Yeah. Well, we'll see about that.

03:41.446 --> 03:43.119
We'll see, all right.

03:43.283 --> 03:45.258
Yeah, we totally will.

03:45.283 --> 03:48.108
Or will we not?

03:48.371 --> 03:50.512
[Stammers] Maybe we won't.

03:50.537 --> 03:51.827
So you're saying we won't?

03:51.852 --> 03:53.072
Yeah.

03:53.132 --> 03:54.970
God damn it, get out of my head, man!

03:54.995 --> 03:56.659
- Whoo!
- Damn it!

03:56.684 --> 03:59.247
You're weak in here.

03:59.272 --> 04:00.489
[Wheezing]

04:00.514 --> 04:02.028
Okay, Yolonzo, where is your inhaler?

04:02.053 --> 04:03.501
Hmm?

04:03.526 --> 04:06.304
Yolonzo, donde esta Tu inhaler?

04:06.972 --> 04:08.734
The Todd.

04:08.759 --> 04:12.139
He made me pay to use.

04:12.164 --> 04:15.809
I give him two sunscreens.

04:15.834 --> 04:18.125
It's not enough.

04:18.149 --> 04:19.535
[Panting]

04:19.560 --> 04:23.594
We are his prisoners!

04:23.819 --> 04:27.851
["Prisoners" echoing]

04:27.876 --> 04:29.262
No, you guys, hear me out.

04:29.287 --> 04:30.771
What if we dug a giant pit?

04:30.796 --> 04:33.046
And make it deep enough so
that nobody can crawl out.

04:33.071 --> 04:35.274
We can throw Todd in there until
he gives us all of our stuff back.

04:35.298 --> 04:37.717
- Pit justice, I like it.
- Yes, finally.

04:37.742 --> 04:39.202
I've been trying to do
that to Todd for years.

04:39.228 --> 04:41.483
No, no, no, no.
What you're talking about is a prison.

04:41.507 --> 04:43.065
Yeah, Flo, face the facts.

04:43.090 --> 04:44.356
Todd took all of our stuff,

04:44.381 --> 04:46.014
and a giant pit is how we get it back.

04:46.108 --> 04:48.075
I mean, come on, you guys.
People are dying here.

04:48.100 --> 04:49.068
Que?!

04:49.093 --> 04:51.210
Pit justice. I'm with Emma.

04:51.235 --> 04:51.782
[Thud] Mm.

04:51.807 --> 04:54.052
You're talking about
putting a man in a hole.

04:54.077 --> 04:56.559
That is a basic human-rights violation.

04:56.584 --> 04:59.010
Ha! Can you guys tell she almost
minored in political science?

04:59.034 --> 04:59.762
Oh!

04:59.787 --> 05:01.128
Okay, for this pit,
what are we thinking?

05:01.153 --> 05:02.272
Beach, jungle?

05:02.297 --> 05:03.671
Who made you leader?

05:03.834 --> 05:06.193
Well, no one is really stepping up here.

05:06.218 --> 05:07.730
Yeah, I think we need an election.

05:07.756 --> 05:10.354
It would be nice for someone
to set some ground rules here.

05:10.379 --> 05:12.784
I just wish there was some
sort of natural leader,

05:12.809 --> 05:14.435
like a lawyer or a doctor.

05:14.460 --> 05:16.275
Turd, I am a doctor!

05:16.300 --> 05:18.714
- Oh, okay.
- Yeah. You know what?

05:18.739 --> 05:20.330
I nominate myself, okay?

05:20.355 --> 05:22.489
I, Emma, nominate myself for leader.

05:22.514 --> 05:25.149
Good, so we can turn
this majestic island

05:25.174 --> 05:27.404
into a North Korean prison state.

05:27.429 --> 05:28.697
I nominate myself.

05:28.722 --> 05:30.092
Florence, come on.
Do you really want to go there?

05:30.117 --> 05:32.832
Oh, I already went there,
and it's friggin' paradise.

05:32.857 --> 05:34.688
That's a good platform.

05:34.713 --> 05:38.382
Oh, electi-o-o-on!!

05:42.941 --> 05:44.480
So, what are we thinking for this pit?

05:44.505 --> 05:45.949
Eight feet, nine feet?

05:46.171 --> 05:47.871
Hell, why don't we just round up to 10?

05:47.896 --> 05:50.782
I like your style, Emma.
You don't pull punches.

05:50.807 --> 05:53.431
The world needs more
dragon bitches like us.

05:53.456 --> 05:55.872
I wouldn't call myself a dragon bitch.
Maybe...

05:55.897 --> 05:57.797
And I'd love to be a
part of your campaign.

05:57.876 --> 05:59.820
Put that black-market
bastard in this hole!

05:59.845 --> 06:02.428
Okay. Uh, well, I can use
all the help I could get.

06:02.453 --> 06:03.577
So welcome aboard.

06:03.602 --> 06:04.995
Now let's cut the shit and get to work.

06:05.020 --> 06:06.773
The election's tonight,
and your hippy-dippy friend

06:06.798 --> 06:08.976
over there is already glad-handing.

06:09.001 --> 06:10.933
[Indistinct conversation, laughter]

06:10.958 --> 06:13.326
It's campaigning time.

06:13.351 --> 06:15.666
Hi. Emma. Can I count
on your vote tonight?

06:15.691 --> 06:17.950
I'm gonna hold you to it.
Gonna hold you to it.

06:17.975 --> 06:20.262
We're family. And family's got to hug.

06:20.287 --> 06:21.273
- Oh.
- Yeah.

06:21.298 --> 06:22.735
Flo is the way to go.

06:22.760 --> 06:25.305
Finally! Someone who understands
the value of the pit.

06:25.330 --> 06:27.784
Oh, yeah.
I can't wait to get Todd in that pit.

06:27.809 --> 06:29.256
- Yeah.
- Start torturing him.

06:29.281 --> 06:30.235
Uh, no.

06:30.260 --> 06:31.809
We're not torturing anyone here.

06:31.834 --> 06:33.220
Oh, right.

06:33.245 --> 06:34.862
We're not torturing anyone here.

06:34.887 --> 06:37.178
We're gonna Guantanamo it. That's smart.

06:37.204 --> 06:38.470
No, still not what I'm saying.

06:38.495 --> 06:39.865
No, no, no, I get what you're saying.

06:39.890 --> 06:42.734
I read you five-by-five.
No torture here whatsoever!

06:42.759 --> 06:44.500
- Yes.
- Wink.

06:44.595 --> 06:47.281
Emma wants to throw Todd in a
prison for taking our stuff.

06:47.306 --> 06:50.191
But isn't having the
stuff the real prison?

06:50.335 --> 06:51.447
[Imitates explosion]

06:51.472 --> 06:53.675
If you don't vote for Emma,
you can go [bleep] yourself.

06:54.645 --> 06:56.518
All right, Margaret, see you tonight.

06:56.543 --> 07:00.213
Tick, tock, tick, tock, tick...

07:00.238 --> 07:03.016
Ahh. You're not gonna wait me out, pal.

07:03.041 --> 07:04.625
I'm not going back to the stuff.

07:04.650 --> 07:08.765
At some point, you're gonna need
food or water or toilet paper.

07:08.790 --> 07:10.508
Oh, will I?

07:10.533 --> 07:13.039
'Cause you happen to
be talking to the guy

07:13.064 --> 07:15.852
that used to shit his pants for laughs.

07:15.876 --> 07:16.938
That's right.

07:16.963 --> 07:20.072
In my fraternity, my
nickname was Streaks.

07:20.171 --> 07:21.603
Pbht!

07:21.628 --> 07:25.278
Right. Jess told me you
guys met at some frat party.

07:25.303 --> 07:26.753
[Scoffs]

07:27.072 --> 07:28.605
Did she now?

07:28.630 --> 07:30.598
You guys were together since college.

07:30.623 --> 07:32.141
That's a pretty long time.

07:32.166 --> 07:33.876
I see what you're doing.

07:34.046 --> 07:37.784
Get me talking about Jess
and her perfect ta-tas

07:37.809 --> 07:39.442
so I break down and cry and shit.

07:39.467 --> 07:44.603
Well, good luck, pal,
'cause I'm a Goddamn rock.

07:47.042 --> 07:49.510
And it wasn't some frat party.

07:49.932 --> 07:51.391
Oh, yeah?

07:51.496 --> 07:55.135
It was the fraternity party of the year.

07:55.160 --> 07:56.401
- [Indistinct shouting]
- [Techno music playing]

07:56.426 --> 07:58.288
Me and the other boys of Beta Gamma Phi

07:58.313 --> 08:01.083
were having our annual
Cowboys and Indians party,

08:01.108 --> 08:04.112
the most legendary party on campus.

08:04.136 --> 08:07.281
I was in the keg corner,
crushing a stand.

08:07.306 --> 08:10.848
Oh, yeah!

08:10.873 --> 08:13.162
I am a god!

08:13.187 --> 08:16.128
- [All chanting "Streaks"]
- 54 seconds... new fraternity record.

08:16.153 --> 08:19.692
[Cheering]

08:19.717 --> 08:21.244
Whoo!

08:21.269 --> 08:22.623
That's when I saw her.

08:22.648 --> 08:25.611
