08:35.407 --> 08:37.523
Hey. Hey.

08:37.548 --> 08:38.543
You heard of me?

08:38.568 --> 08:40.410
- No.
- [Scoffs]

08:40.436 --> 08:41.741
Yeah, right.

08:41.767 --> 08:43.308
Todd: And she was the only girl

08:43.335 --> 08:44.831
that wouldn't take any of my guff.

08:44.856 --> 08:46.057
I like your costume.

08:46.082 --> 08:47.830
Hey, thanks.

08:47.855 --> 08:50.562
I'm the wrong Indian.

08:50.911 --> 08:52.110
Cute.

08:52.135 --> 08:54.739
- You a freshman?
- Yeah, just turned 18.

08:54.764 --> 08:55.804
You a senior?

08:55.829 --> 08:56.963
Fifth year.

08:56.988 --> 08:58.454
Cool.

08:58.490 --> 09:01.581
Later that night, we banged.

09:01.606 --> 09:03.631
[Both moaning]

09:04.808 --> 09:07.066
Tale as old as time.

09:07.091 --> 09:09.060
[Retches]

09:09.520 --> 09:13.288
Yeah. We hooked up for,
like, two years after that.

09:13.313 --> 09:15.213
Been officially together for seven.

09:15.238 --> 09:17.404
Well, we were.

09:17.429 --> 09:20.396
Hey, it's not too late to get Jess back.

09:20.421 --> 09:22.943
You just got to show
us where the stuff is.

09:24.874 --> 09:28.542
No! I know what you're doing,
playing your mind games.

09:28.567 --> 09:30.928
Well, you can eat a butt and go to hell.

09:30.953 --> 09:32.946
You know what? This ends right now.

09:33.252 --> 09:35.650
We're gonna settle this
the fraternity way...

09:35.794 --> 09:37.424
Like gentlemen.

09:41.122 --> 09:43.185
Classic drink-off.

09:43.560 --> 09:45.594
You win, I give you back all the stuff.

09:45.619 --> 09:47.164
I win...

09:47.719 --> 09:51.586
you leave me alone and I get your gun.

09:52.907 --> 09:56.156
That's right, your baby.

09:56.436 --> 09:59.288
Come on, Danny boy.
You want to be a hero, don't you?

09:59.717 --> 10:01.377
What do you say?

10:01.996 --> 10:04.224
Let's have a little drinky, drinky.

10:04.249 --> 10:07.168
â™ª

10:07.491 --> 10:09.136
I did a little informal polling.

10:09.161 --> 10:09.621
Okay.

10:09.646 --> 10:11.445
There's about a dozen
people who are pro-pit.

10:11.470 --> 10:12.781
You'll definitely get those votes.

10:12.806 --> 10:13.584
Okay, great.

10:13.609 --> 10:15.180
But Florence has about double that.

10:15.205 --> 10:16.339
Wait, how?

10:16.364 --> 10:17.662
Well, she doesn't offer any solutions,

10:17.687 --> 10:19.930
but people like her,
and the voters find you,

10:19.955 --> 10:22.192
well, smug and condescending.

10:22.253 --> 10:24.622
Condescending? Really?
They find me condescending?

10:24.647 --> 10:26.325
Idiots.

10:26.350 --> 10:27.625
This is why Hillary struggles.

10:27.650 --> 10:28.750
You know, people are afraid

10:28.776 --> 10:30.797
of a smart, strong, independent woman.

10:30.822 --> 10:32.475
Yeah, I hear you, sister.

10:32.500 --> 10:34.998
You, me, Hillary, we're all the same.

10:35.023 --> 10:37.135
It's like looking in a friggin' mirror.

10:37.642 --> 10:40.309
Okay, you know what?
Florence isn't even saying anything.

10:40.334 --> 10:41.633
You know, she's all just like...

10:41.658 --> 10:43.643
[Imitating Florence]
"One world, one love."

10:43.668 --> 10:44.835
I can't lose.

10:44.860 --> 10:47.761
Okay, I don't lose,
especially not to Florence.

10:47.786 --> 10:49.074
Well, I hate to tell you,

10:49.100 --> 10:50.750
you're probably gonna have to pander.

10:50.775 --> 10:51.874
Dumb it down a little.

10:51.899 --> 10:53.589
No, I'm not gonna dumb it down.

10:56.331 --> 10:58.056
What if we got a Nader?

10:58.081 --> 11:00.418
You know, like some
wild-card third party

11:00.443 --> 11:01.753
that could split up the old idiot vote.

11:01.778 --> 11:04.008
Yes! A likable dummy.

11:04.033 --> 11:05.464
- Mm-hmm.
- But who?

11:05.489 --> 11:07.418
Steve: You know,
I've always been a hit with the birds.

11:07.527 --> 11:10.899
Oh! Oh, I guess Polly wants a ginger!

11:12.122 --> 11:13.946
[Laughs] Hi, Emma!

11:13.971 --> 11:16.500
â™ª

11:19.350 --> 11:20.603
What if it was Steve?

11:20.629 --> 11:22.657
Yep, that's what that look was for.

11:22.682 --> 11:23.815
Mm-hmm.

11:30.754 --> 11:32.254
Karen: Hey.

11:32.289 --> 11:33.922
Hey. I don't know about you,

11:33.957 --> 11:35.824
but this food's getting a bit "boaring."

11:35.859 --> 11:37.151
I acknowledge your pun.

11:37.176 --> 11:38.152
Look, Steve, there's something

11:38.177 --> 11:39.581
I'd like to talk to you about.

11:39.606 --> 11:40.421
Okay.

11:40.446 --> 11:42.117
I think you should
run for island leader.

11:42.142 --> 11:45.146
[Giggles] Oh! That's rich, Karen.

11:45.171 --> 11:46.269
Thanks for the chortle.

11:46.294 --> 11:48.258
Steve, do I look like I'm joking?

11:49.537 --> 11:51.096
No.

11:51.201 --> 11:53.353
[Sighs] But me?

11:53.378 --> 11:55.423
Run against Florence and Emma?

11:55.448 --> 11:57.049
People don't listen to me.

11:57.074 --> 11:58.869
These people would.
Everyone here likes you.

11:58.895 --> 12:01.075
You have a very nonthreatening face.

12:01.100 --> 12:04.418
Well, thank you. It's almost kind.

12:04.616 --> 12:06.234
I don't know.

12:07.006 --> 12:09.463
I've never been in a position of power.

12:09.489 --> 12:12.275
The way I see it, people think of me

12:12.299 --> 12:14.602
as some kind of a joke, you know?

12:14.627 --> 12:18.629
Steve, here, we could be different.

12:19.057 --> 12:20.890
What do you want to be?

12:21.322 --> 12:24.028
â™ª

12:24.053 --> 12:25.315
The rules are simple.

12:25.688 --> 12:28.502
First one to pass out,
shit their pants, or puke loses.

12:28.527 --> 12:31.409
